#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "**8 MAR \\| Across Uganda, DRC, Nigeria & The Gambia** \n"
msgstr "**三月八号\\| 乌干达，刚果民主共和国，尼日利亚和冈比亚** \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:84
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image5.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image5.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:86
msgid ""
"[XR Uganda](https://twitter.com/XREA15) organised a **Women’s March** in "
"Mbale as part of [International Women's Day 2020](https://www."
"internationalwomensday.com/Theme), planting trees and teaching children "
"about the Emergency."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:88
msgid ""
"Rebels highlighted how climate and ecological breakdown will impact women "
"and the poorest communities the most. Women, such as those in [Bududa]"
"(https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N9THGtqjnv0), have been left ‘[without "
"anything](https://reliefweb.int/report/uganda/bugisu-landslide-survivors-"
"struggle-cope-life) - homeless, helpless, hopeless by unpredictable rains, "
"floods and [mud slides](https://reliefweb.int/report/uganda/over-30-people-"
"feared-dead-fresh-bududa-mudslide).’"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:90
msgid ""
"Their situation is made worse by prolonged droughts, higher temperatures, "
"increased crop failure, loss of livestock and increasing food insecurity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:92
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image6.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image6.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:94
msgid ""
"The Mbale march also focussed on **the need for access to quality "
"education**. When breakdown and instability hit, more children are forced to "
"abandon their education and more girls are [pressured into child marriage]"
"(https://www.bridesofthesun.com)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:96
msgid ""
"The **brave women** of Uganda are refusing to stand by and watch their "
"future and their children’s future be lost. To achieve **Climate Justice, we "
"must focus on Social Justice**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:98
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image7.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image7.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:100
#, no-wrap
msgid " *Mugunga, DRC*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:102
msgid ""
"Indigenous women in **XR Hewa Bora** surrounded a park warden camp and "
"demanded an end to climate rape and sexual violence in the forest."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:104
msgid ""
"[XR Abuja](https://twitter.com/AbujaXr) celebrated International Women’s Day "
"in **Nigeria** and held discussions around the challenges women face as a "
"result of the climate **crisis** and the need for equality."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:105
#, no-wrap
msgid "Breaking Waves at Venice Carnival"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "**20-25 FEB \\| Venice, Italy**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:110
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image8.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image8.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:112
msgid ""
"The **first Wave of Global Rebellion hit the canals of Venice** last month, "
"with rebels from across Italy carrying out a series of spectacular actions "
"during the city’s annual carnival."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:114
msgid ""
"The protests kicked off with [a blindfolded flash mob performance](https://"
"youtu.be/s4Yk-16gfrY). **Blindfolded rebels** stood in solemn silence as a "
"speaker called on the carnival revellers to open their eyes to the climate "
"crisis, and join their rebellion."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:116
msgid ""
"Two days later, hundreds of rebels flooded the busy Venetian streets for a "
"spot of joyful [discobedience](https://youtu.be/86SrCcx_zXY)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:118
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image9.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image9.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:120
msgid ""
"The next morning, a group of rebels [blockaded the Ponte dell’Accademia]"
"(https://youtu.be/i8CLLhGJ_eA), a bridge spanning the city’s Grand Canal."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:122
#, no-wrap
msgid "**The lock-in marked one of the first high-risk actions for XR Italy**. Tensions were high as the rebels fitted into their arm tubes, but thanks to heartfelt chants and open dialogue, the blockade continued without violence.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:124
msgid ""
"Venice is made up of more than 100 islands inside a lagoon and has already "
"suffered extensive damage from the climate crisis. Much of the ancient city "
"is [flooded](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-50401308) year after "
"year."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:126
msgid "Will Venice become our next Atlantis?"
msgstr "威尼斯会成为下一个亚特兰蒂斯吗？"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:128
msgid ""
"Yet the Italian government and local authorities have **still not declared** "
"a climate emergency. Without major policy change, the UNESCO world heritage "
"site appears doomed. Or as the Italian rebels put it: ‘[There’s no carnival "
"under the sea](https://extinctionrebellion.it/notizie/press/2020/02/19/no-"
"carnevale-in-fondo-al-mare/)’."
msgstr ""
"然而意大利政府和当地官员**依然没有宣布**气候危机的存在。没有政策变动，联合国"
"教科文组织的世界遗产似乎面临着不可避免的厄运。用意大利反叛者们的话来说就"
"是“[海底下可办不了狂欢节](https://extinctionrebellion.it/notizie/"
"press/2020/02/19/no-carnevale-in-fondo-al-mare/)”。"

#. type: Title ###
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:129
#, no-wrap
msgid "Indigenous Pipeline Protests sweep Canada"
msgstr "加拿大管道工程大抗议"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:132
#, no-wrap
msgid "**FEB \\| British Columbia, Canada**\n"
msgstr "**二月 \\| 不列颠哥伦比亚省，加拿大**\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:134
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image10.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image10.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:136
#, no-wrap
msgid " *Photo by Darryl Dyck / Canadian Press*\n"
msgstr " *Darryl Dyck 摄 / 加拿大通讯社*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:138
msgid ""
"An ongoing surge of [civil disobedience](https://www.theguardian.com/"
"world/2020/feb/28/canada-pipeline-protests-climate-indigenous-rights) rolled "
"across Canada in February. Protests began in British Columbia, where "
"Wet'suwet'en hereditary chiefs blocked railways to [protest the construction]"
"(https://www.thenation.com/article/activism/indigenous-resistance-wetsuweten-"
"canada/) of a multi-billion-dollar pipeline through their unceded territory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:140
msgid ""
"After [disturbing reports](https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/10/"
"canada-protest-indigenous-wetsuweten-pipeline) of forceful removal by police "
"(as well as possible illegal restraint), these actions gained traction with "
"Indigenous and solidarity protestors."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:142
msgid ""
"Meanwhile, in Ontario and Quebec, Mohawks disrupted rail networks; in "
"Vancouver, **38 people were arrested** for blocking access to shipping "
"ports; in Toronto, **37 were arrested** for bringing the city's Union "
"Station to a standstill at rush hour."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:144
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image11.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image11.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:146
#, no-wrap
msgid " *Photo by Canadian Press/REX/Shutterstock*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:148
msgid ""
"Much of this burgeoning civil disobedience has taken **inspiration from the "
"initial actions of the Wet'suwet'en chiefs**, with the focus point of "
"strategy being rail blockades. This has caused disruption to construction "
"work, passenger and freight transport, and to the Canadian economy at large."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:150
msgid ""
"The scale of disruption is [clearly evident](https://theturtleislandnews.com/"
"index.php/2020/02/14/cn-shuts-down-eastern-rail-network-via-service-due-to-"
"anti-pipeline-blockades/) with the news that Canada's two largest railways "
"have been [covertly sharing railway links](https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/"
"cp-cn-arrangement-blockade-1.5474684), and have diverted some key routes "
"through the US."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:152
msgid ""
"The impact of this story has extended far beyond Canada with protests "
"gaining support from groups all around the world."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "‘Cheers to the end of the world!’"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:156
#, no-wrap
msgid "**1 MAR \\| Lamma Island, Hong Kong**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:158
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image12.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image12.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:160
#, no-wrap
msgid " *Dining in the South China Sea, Lamma Island, Hong Kong*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:162
msgid ""
"On a sunny Sunday afternoon, XRHK staged a ‘[dinner party](https://www."
"hongkongfp.com/2020/03/02/extinction-rebellion-stages-formal-dinner-party-"
"south-china-sea-highlight-climate-crisis/)’ off a Hong Kong Beach among the "
"waves as a reminder that – even though the media has shifted its attention "
"to the coronavirus – we are **still facing catastrophic ecological and "
"climate breakdown**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:164
msgid ""
"With the coal-fired Hong Kong power station as backdrop, **rebels "
"impersonated the 1%, “cheering to the end of the world as we know it**, "
"partying while climate change and associated natural disasters already kill "
"the poorest and most vulnerable.”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:166
msgid ""
"Specifically, rebels intended to highlight [Hong Kong’s vulnerability, as a "
"coastal city, to sea-level changes](http://www.chinawaterrisk.org/resources/"
"analysis-reviews/thirsty-and-underwater-rising-risks-in-greater-bay-area/), "
"and the city’s lack of a viable strategy to address the looming crisis. “The "
"adopted strategy – to replace one fossil fuel by another, in this case coal "
"by natural gas – is, while less carbon-intensive, ultimately highly "
"counterproductive,’"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:168
msgid ""
"To read more on XRHK follow them [here](https://www.facebook.com/"
"extinctionrebellionHK/) or [here](https://twitter.com/XRHongKong)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:169
#, no-wrap
msgid "Heathrow victory for Earth protectors!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:172
#, no-wrap
msgid "**27 FEB \\| London, UK**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:174
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image13.jpg)"
msgstr "![](/assets/uploads/2020-03-13-newsletter-37-image13.jpg)"

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:176
msgid ""
"Plans to expand Heathrow airport [were ruled illegal](https://www."
"theguardian.com/environment/2020/feb/27/heathrow-third-runway-ruled-illegal-"
"over-climate-change) because they clashed with the government’s commitments "
"to tackle the climate crisis. The government must now either make a new "
"proposal that is in line with the UK’s environmental targets or withdraw it "
"entirely."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:178
msgid ""
"This exciting ruling by the British Court of Appeal has global implications. "
"It is **the first time that climate targets made under the Paris Agreement "
"have carried legal weight**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-03-13-newsletter-37.md:180
msgid ""
"The success of this court ruling gives some hope to the implementation of "
"the Paris targets. If any other of the 188 nations that are party to the "
"Agreement now green lights a high-carbon infrastructure project, **there is "
"a legal precedent to challenge the decision**."
msgstr ""

